{
  "doc_id": "20429",
  "text": "Renal cell carcinoma frequently metastasizes to the lumen of the IVC, but seminoma can also mimic this picture. Case reports exist of IVC involvement on initial presentation, although involvement is more typically found after diagnosis [CITATION_1] . In a 20-year retrospective review of testicular cancer patients at a single institution, the incidence of intraluminal thrombus at postchemotherapy retroperitoneal lymph node dissection was found to be 5.8% [CITATION_2] . The study identified 89 postchemotherapy patients with 98 intraluminal thrombi (72 IVC, 20 renal vein, and 1 aorta), and active malignancy was found in approximately 45%. Of the patients with intraluminal thrombus, one-half eventually required vena cavectomy for curative treatment.",
